main event: A single white circular object was observed in Chicago, Illinois on 23 October 1932.
interesting points: The object was viewed for 2-3 minutes,The object moved in an erratic manner without lights or propulsion system,At one point the object faded out and then reappeared,The object was silent and estimated to be faster than conventional aircraft,The report classifies the event as an unidentified aerial phenomenon.
witness description: civilian pilot, Air Force reserve lieutenant
